  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Swimming Pool Maintenance Engineer",
  "description": "<h2><strong>Swimming Pool Maintenance Engineer</strong></h2><h3><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Carry out routine inspection, maintenance, and servicing of swimming pools, spa pools, water features, and related systems</p></li><li><p>Monitor and maintain water quality (pH, chlorine, alkalinity) in accordance with NEA and PUB guidelines</p></li><li><p>Perform backwashing, filter maintenance, pump and motor checks, and basic troubleshooting</p></li><li><p>Attend to corrective maintenance, breakdowns, and emergency call-outs when required</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate maintenance records, checklists, and service reports</p></li><li><p>Coordinate with contractors and suppliers for repair works and chemical supplies</p></li><li><p>Ensure compliance with workplace safety, health regulations, and environmental standards</p></li><li><p>Support audits, inspections, and handovers for MCSTs or property owners</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p><strong>At least 1–3 years of relevant experience</strong> in swimming pool maintenance (commercial / condominium preferred)</p></li><li><p>Knowledge of <strong>pool circulation systems, filtration, dosing systems, and water treatment</strong></p></li><li><p>Able to read basic M&E drawings and equipment manuals</p></li><li><p>Possess good troubleshooting and hands-on maintenance skills</p></li><li><p>Willing to work weekends, public holidays, or attend emergency calls when required</p></li><li><p>Physically fit and comfortable working in wet or outdoor environments</p></li></ul>",
